<p class="text-primary m-10 text-lg">In <span class="italic">"This World Is Made for Monsters"</span> (<a href="/references" class="link link-info">Rickert, 2020</a>), the 
    theme of xenophobia is prevalent throughout the narrative, shaping the characters' reactions to the 
    aliens and influencing their behavior. From the moment the spaceship lands, fear and prejudice are 
    evident among the townspeople, leading to tragic consequences and highlighting the destructive 
    impact of xenophobia on individuals and communities. The townspeople's initial reactions to the arrival 
    of the aliens are marked by confusion and panic. The narrator describes how the mothers run after their 
    children to ensure their safety, while the fathers attempt to secure their families and homes. This fear 
    of the unknown sets the stage for a series of misunderstandings and mistrust that escalate throughout 
    the story.</p>

